At no time did I say I never used spells for agro.  I did, frequently, to the point of mana depletion if I didn't have KEI.  The point I was making was that offensive equipment has a huge boost to agro.<br>
<br>
Back in the day, around level 54 or so ish, playing in PoN I was beggining to find I was struggling to keep agro and was reduced to chain casting CD.  In order to counter this I worked for and obtained a better haste item and a bigger weapon after which I had to be careful not to get agro in those groups where I was just a.n.other melee.<br>
<br>
Your offensive equipment has a huge effect on the agro you generate, and any player of a knight class who says it is all down to play skill and how often you cast stun/darkness is just a gimp with crap gear.<br>
<br>
Anyone can get reasonable gear, and in doing so generate sufficient agro to contribute more to the group either in agro'ing additional loose mobs in an ACC role or by increasing their DPS by not having to chain cast.<br>
<br>
As for playing for maximum XP and not fun.  Fun was never the subject of the rant.  I used to have a lot of fun in EQ, I stopped when I got bored of it, but that wasn't because I played an SK well or played an SK badly, I just got bored of the game having played it for 3 or so years.  Just because a player like myself like to push the limits of gameplay does not meen I cannot have fun doing so, it just meens I get more reward from the game whilst having that fun.<br>
