<br>
I have better than a FBSS, a windblade, and keep 2 tap procs going at all times.  SOMETIMES I use my darkness in LDoN, but considering how fast we usually kill these mobs, it is almost never needed UNLESS a nuke pulls the mob of of me.  Then, and ONLY THEN, I feel that I need to use my snare since someone is so close to me on the hatelist that not doing it may casue a pong.<br>
(1) This adds about 450+ points to my agro listing and pushes me ahead of everyone else.<br>
(2) In CASE someone takes agro off of me, the mob turns and slowly walks after the culprit as I jolt his ass and get agro back on me.<br>
(3) Jolt, taunt, nuke, proceed to shove a red hot pepper up the mob's ass.  It's not that hard to figure out.<br>
<br>
In case the mob hits hard enough that I think the healer can't keep up, I use bond of death.  It gives me 80 of the mob's hitpoints per tick adn allows the healer a little extra time to get that heal off.  Also, I hve two 50 point procs loaded at all times, and they go off OFTEN (agility farging rules!).  <br>
<br>
Yes, ther have been particullarly tough mobs that I had to use a mod rod after for.  That happens.  But for the most part, once I figured out what my spells were for, how they worked, and what I needed to do to tank, it made all the difference.  Ifind that I hold agro BETTER with a smaller faster weapon and my shield than I do with my windblade.  What makes the difference is whether or not we have the nuke power to make up for the drop in DPS.  It's not all about speed, you have to think, adjust, and overcome.<br>
Believe it or don't, but that is part of being a tank.<br>
<br>
And since you bring it up ....<br>
It's not always one at a time.  SOMETIMES it is 3 at a time, sometimes 4.  NOW, since not many people will stand very long with that much DPS on them, I usually let one get on me and hope the changer/cleric/druid/shammy (whoever) can mez/root the rest.  If it breaks, I can snare the one I am on and go tank the other if need be, or let the casters deal with it.  My job (you understnad that word, right?  Job?) is to keep the mob on me long enough to let the casters kill it.  I have seen clerics and wizards blast mobs for 20k plus... I can't come NEAR that, but I can buy them the time to do it.<br>
If you love raids so much, more power to you.  I can't fucking stand them.  I find NO skill at throwing man after woman after man at a mob until it finally drops.  Telling me you are so great becasue you play like some Ebay noob fails to impress me, and actually makes me feel sorry for those associated with you.  say what you like, but every word from you so far has been the same warmed over bullshit I have come to expect from people that have NO idea how to play.<br>
<br>
Case in point:<br>
A little more than a year ago I was looking at a guild led by an ex-guildmate.  I wasn't extremely impressed with them, but had friends in the guild, so I figured I would check them out.  We went into a room in Kael with about 40 (maybe more) people and just cleared the zone again and again and again.<br>
Last week I went to the SAME room with a different guild (mine) and about 10 people, IF that many.  We did better better and had way more fun.<br>
Gear?  Nope?<br>
Levels? Nope, most of us were younger the second time.<br>
Sony nerfed the zone?  Nope, they actually tweaked it to two pops instead of one at a time.<br>
Then we were all &quot;OMG Ubah 7eeL twinks&quot;, right?  WRONG... most of us (me included) will tell you what gimps we are.<br>
<br>
We have learned to work together and work as a team.  We know our classes and how to make it all come together.  Yeah, we had to use raid grouping, but I would HARDLY call about 10 people (if 10) a raid.  It was NOT single tanking all out, but we were able to adjust and overcome each pull and pop without fail.  THAT is what I call good tanking, and it means WAY more than just having &quot;teh 7eeL gears&quot;. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tibult>tibult</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www-personal.umich.edu/~nnettles/Nick1.gif" BORDER=0> at: 11/24/03 1:08 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=baldrikthedorf>Baldrik the Dorf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.josh-leclair.com/uploads/docs/fairy_bounce08.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ANGRY. rar.</span><br>  Posts: 739<br> <font color=#330000>(11/24/03 1:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1154.topic&index=75>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: heh</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Everything else being equal, according to Tibult an SK or Pally with an FBSS and a short sword of the Ykesha can hold agro as well as I could when I played. At least that is the argument he is raising.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
